Russians have been warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from fraudsters who replace the phone number of the bank has increased.
This is reported by Kommersant with reference to the data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator passed information to the telecommunications operators about more than 2,500 numbers, from which customers of various financial organizations were called.
In 189 cases, the operators found a replacement number.
A further 218 numbers were blocked, and in 59 cases the use of financial services was restricted.
The deputy head of the information security department of the Central Bank Artem Sychev said that a wide range of Russian banks faced with the replacement of the number.
He explained that operators do not always respond to the Central Bank’s warnings about fraudulent calls, citing the absence of such an obligation in the Communications Act.
At the Opening Bank, Rosbank and Alpha Bank confirmed the information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with the replacement of the number.
According to the Biline press service, part of the information about fraudulent calls that the Central Bank gave was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are actually used by banks to communicate with customers.
Their blocking would lead to failures in the work of the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of fraudster numbers, which the telecommunications operator will contact with each call to check the number.
He explained that such a basis would require amendments to the legislation.
