Russia's "sanctions" have fallen 100 times
The Russian government has estimated that the supply of agricultural products and food to Russia from countries that fell under the Russian food embargo has decreased more than 100 times since 2013.
According to the report sent to Russian President Vladimir Putin, in the first half of 2019, 31 thousand tons of products were imported from the sanctioned countries against 3 million 442.2 thousand tons for the same period of 2013, Interfax reports.
At the same time, the value of imported products decreased to $226,5 million from $4 billion to $975.5 million, respectively.
We are talking about deliveries of goods that have not been burned under the embargo.
As indicated in the report, the fallen volumes of prohibited imports were offset by an increase in imports from CIS countries, Africa, South-East Asia, Serbia.
At the end of August, the government extended until December 31, 2020, the validity of the rules for the destruction of agricultural products, raw materials and food, which are prohibited to import into Russia under counter-sanctions.
The document, posted on the official portal of legal information, noted that the validity of the rules has been extended for another year - from December 31, 2019 to December 31, 2020.
Initially, the order to abolish the sanctions applied to products from the United States, the EU, Australia, Norway and Canada.
Later, on August 13, 2015, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland and Liechtenstein joined this list, and on January 1, 2016 – Ukraine.
The decree signed by Putin on the destruction of illegally imported “sanctions” (products that fell under a food embargo, which Moscow imposed in response to anti-Russian sanctions of the West) came into force in 2015.
In turn, the government has allowed the destruction of “sanctioned” food by any lawful means.
As Western sanctions continue, Russia has also extended its retaliatory measures.
At the same time, products that citizens import for personal use, this measure does not apply.
The ban does not apply to the importation of goods for personal consumption weighing up to 5 kilograms.
However, the head of the Council under the President of the Russian Federation on the development of civil society and human rights, Mikhail Fedotov, previously called the destruction of food products "simplely immoral", and this, according to him, negatively affects the education of people.
Moreover, Rospotrebnadzor took the initiative to ban the destruction of foods suitable for consumption at the beginning of June.
After that, a similar recommendation was made to the Government by the Human Rights Council under the President of the Russian Federation.
And Deputy Prime Minister of the Russian Federation Alexei Gordeyev said that it is wrong to destroy food, and it is necessary to think about how you can use them as intended, assessing the quality.
The head of the company is found guilty of tax evasion
By the verdict of the Leninsky District Court of the city of Cheboksary, the director of the LLC "Land and Law" Vyacheslav Morozov is found guilty of committing the crimes provided for in paragraph "b" of Article 199 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (evasion from the payment of taxes from the organization by inclusion in the tax declaration of the accused).
This is reported by the press service of the investigative department of the SCR for Chuvashia.
From January 2008 to December 2009, Vyacheslav Morozov entered in the documents of the tax accounting LLC information about imperfect transactions.
According to the fictitious documents, the company incurred additional costs, and, therefore, the amount of taxes payable on value added and profits of the organization was reduced by 11.2 million rubles.
Vyacheslav Morozov was sentenced to 3.5 years in prison on parole.
By 2023, the first school of the new format will open in the center of the capital
The new school will open in Khamovniki.
According to the head of Moscomstroyinvest, Anastasia Pyatova, there will be all the conditions for the self-realization and development of children’s talents.
The educational institution decided to call the "New Look".
This project will be supervised by the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia and the Foundation "Economic Development of Higher School".
The design of the building with an area of about 10,000 "squares" is planned to begin as early as next year.
Construction will be completed at the end of 2022, and the next will begin to recruit the first students.
"The project provides for the creation of a public, non-profit educational space, which will be based on the traditions of the classical Moscow school and experimental methods," - noted in the press service of Moscomstroyinvest.
In Chile, began to build a telescope worth 1 billion euros
This is reported by TASS with reference to the press service of the European Southern Observatory (ESO).
According to ESO, the building’s dome, which will house the European Extremely Large Telescope (E-ELT), has officially begun construction this week, and is the most expensive and ambitious ground-based astronomical project.
Its total value is estimated by ESO to exceed <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>1 billion.
Most of this money will be spent on equipment and building the observatory building.
The most expensive and complex component of the telescope is its record-large mirror, whose diameter will be about 39 meters.
It will be assembled from 798 hexagonal segments measuring 1.4 meters.
This huge mirror, as well as two auxiliary reflective surfaces with a diameter of 4.2 and 3.75 meters, will help the E-ELT to get the first detailed photos of planets outside the solar system, stars in other galaxies, and to look for Earth's twins.
In addition, scientists will try to use this observatory to observe the vicinity of Sgr A*, a supermassive black hole in the center of the Milky Way.
Despite the fact that the construction of the dome is only beginning, the mirrors, scientific tools and other components of the observatory scientists, engineers and other specialists have been developing for three years - since the announcement of the first plans for the construction of the E-ELT.
The contract for the production of the main mirror, whose total value was about 400 million euros, was received by the German company SCHOTT and the French company Safran Reosc.
